oracle.spatial.hadoop.vector.mapreduce.input

Class WrapperInputFormat<I,J,K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • <any>
      • oracle.spatial.hadoop.vector.mapreduce.input.WrapperInputFormat<I,J,K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - The type of the record's key. The same used by internalInputFormat
    V - The type of the record's value. The same used by internalInputFormat.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FileSplitInputFormat, PointKeyInputFormat, SpatialFilterInputFormat

    public abstract class WrapperInputFormat<I,J,K,V>
extends <any>
    Abstract InputFormat which uses another InputFormat (internalInputFormat) to read data and allows adding additional functionality such as spatial filtering. The internal input format must be a subclass of FileInputFormat.
    Author:
    hsaucedo

      • getFittingInputSplit

        public static InputSplit getFittingInputSplit(JobContext context,
                                              <any> inputFormat,
                                              InputSplit split)
                                       throws java.io.IOException
        Returns an instance of an InputSplit subclass appropriate for the given InputFormat. For example, if the passed split is a FileSplit instance and the InputFormat is a CombineFileInputFormat implementation, the returned split will be a instance of CombineFileSplit.
        Parameters:
        context - the job configuration
        inputFormat - an InputFormat instance
        split - an InputSplit instance
        Returns:
        if the passed split fits the input format, it is returned, otherwise a new one that fits is returned.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
